================================================================================
SECTION 2: COMPLETION & SUCCESS ANIMATIONS (LIGHT MODE)
================================================================================

2.1 CHECKBOX COMPLETION ANIMATION
----------------------------------

The checkbox is the MOST FREQUENT animation in a TODO app. It must feel
satisfying without becoming annoying after the 1000th tap.

PHASE 1: Tap Recognition (0-50ms)
  - Scale checkbox to 0.92 (press feedback)
  - Background shifts from transparent to rgba(184,134,11,0.08) -- subtle gold wash
  - Haptic: UIImpactFeedbackGenerator.light (iOS) / HapticFeedback.lightImpact (Flutter)

PHASE 2: Fill Animation (50-250ms)
  - Checkbox border color transitions: #1A053340 -> #B8860B (gold)
  - Fill sweeps from center outward (radial wipe, not opacity fade)
  - Fill color: solid #B8860B (rich gold -- high contrast on #F8F5FF)
  - Checkmark draws with stroke animation (SVG path or Rive)
  - Checkmark color: #FFFFFF (white on gold = excellent contrast)
  - Easing: Curves.easeOutBack (slight overshoot for satisfaction)

PHASE 3: Ripple Expansion (200-400ms)
  - NOT a glow -- a WASH expansion
  - Circular wash: rgba(184,134,11,0.06) expands from checkbox center
  - Radius expands from 20px to 80px, opacity fades from 0.06 to 0.00
  - This replaces the "glow pulse" used in dark mode

PHASE 4: Text Strikethrough (250-450ms)
  - Strikethrough line wipes left-to-right
  - Line color: #6B21A8 (deep purple -- MORE visible than gold on white)
  - Line thickness: 1.5px (not 1px -- needs visibility on light bg)
  - Text opacity transitions: 1.0 -> 0.5 (not 0.3 -- must stay readable)
  - Duration: 200ms, Curve: Curves.easeInOut

PHASE 5: Settle (400-550ms)
  - Scale returns to 1.0 from slight 1.02 overshoot
  - All colors reach final state
  - Total animation: ~550ms (within the 200-500ms best practice sweet spot,
    slightly extended for multi-phase richness)

Why these choices:
  - Gold fill provides strong contrast ratio (4.8:1) against #F8F5FF
  - Purple strikethrough (not gold) because purple has higher luminance
    contrast against the near-white background
  - Wash expansion (not glow) because additive glow is invisible on light
  - Text stays at 0.5 opacity (not 0.3) for light-mode readability

Real-world examples:
  - Things 3: Uses a simple fill + checkmark draw, minimal but satisfying
  - Todoist: Red circle fill with white check, quick 200ms, no post-effects
  - TickTick: Colorful fill matching priority, includes a tiny "pop" scale
  - Apple Reminders: Blue fill, checkmark draws, subtle scale bounce
  - SurveyMonkey: Checkbox with checkmark appearance + strike-through effect

Competitive edge for UNJYNX: The wash expansion + gold fill + purple
strikethrough combo is unique. No major competitor uses a two-color completion
(gold check + purple strikethrough) or the wash ripple technique.

2.2 PROJECT/MILESTONE COMPLETION CELEBRATION
---------------------------------------------

When ALL tasks in a project are done, a bigger celebration triggers:

OPTION A: Confetti Burst (recommended for light mode)
  - 40-60 particles (NOT 100+ like dark mode -- less is more on light)
  - Particle colors: #B8860B (gold), #6B21A8 (deep purple), #1A0533 (midnight),
    #D4A847 (lighter gold), #9333EA (medium purple)
  - NO pastel particles -- they vanish on #F8F5FF
  - Each particle: 4-8px, mix of circles and rectangles
  - Physics: gravity 980px/s^2, initial velocity 400-800px/s upward
  - Spread angle: 120 degrees from center-top
  - Duration: 1200ms total, particles fade at 800ms+
  - Background: brief flash of rgba(184,134,11,0.04) across full screen

OPTION B: Progress Ring Burst
  - Project progress ring THICKENS from 4px to 12px
  - Shimmer sweeps along the ring (gradient: #B8860B -> #D4A847 -> #B8860B)
  - Ring color shifts from tracking purple to celebration gold
  - Small "spark" particles (5-8) emit from the ring completion point
  - Ring then settles back to normal thickness with gold color

For UNJYNX, use Option A for major milestones (project complete) and
Option B for sub-milestones (all tasks in a section done).

A subtle celebration animation after completing a significant task can boost
satisfaction, though the same animation repeated frequently becomes an obstacle
to efficiency. This is why UNJYNX uses a tiered system: frequent completions
(individual tasks) get quick animations, rare completions (projects) get
celebrations.

2.3 STREAK MILESTONE CELEBRATION
---------------------------------

Referencing Duolingo's approach (they treat milestones like "power ups"
with the character physically changing on exciting days):

  - Streak flame icon: Rive animation with warm gradient (#B8860B -> #D4763B)
  - On light bg, the flame needs a SHADOW ANCHOR:
    - Drop shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(26,5,51,0.15) beneath the flame
    - This "grounds" the flame on the light surface (prevents floating look)
  - Milestone numbers (7, 30, 100 days): animated_flip_counter with gold digits
  - Background: brief warm wash rgba(184,134,11,0.06) behind the streak card
  - Haptic: UINotificationFeedbackGenerator.success
  - Apps combining streaks + milestones see 40-60% higher DAU compared to
    single-feature implementations (Plotline research)

Sources:
- Duolingo Streak Animation Blog: https://blog.duolingo.com/streak-milestone-design-animation/
- BricxLabs Micro Animation Examples: https://bricxlabs.com/blogs/micro-interactions-2025-examples
- Mockplus Button State Design: https://www.mockplus.com/blog/post/button-state-design
- Justinmind Micro-interactions: https://www.justinmind.com/web-design/micro-interactions
- Plotline Streaks Gamification: https://www.plotline.so/blog/streaks-for-gamification-in-mobile-apps
